column5: Wow !!!...Was the water ever down...the log in the foreground is normally submerged...this next pic was taken on the 15th April 2013...

I hope levels are down this year, We didn't have any beach here after all the snow in the winter of 13', 14'. Many rocks were only inches or just below water levels making boating close the shoreline dangerous when normally they can be seen. Will have to wait and see. Still no open water today off Hoovers Point, Lake Erie.
Another shot of the shoreline towards the little island...
No fear of the creek overflowing...
Lotsa water going through the dams at Youngs Point & Lakefield Norm, maybe I should sneak over there tonight and shut them down a little bit for ya. LOL
chemong has bays dry.  Isnt this getting kind of crazy that they are not bringing them back up

Maribeth told me that one of her friends said that the rocks below the dam in 'Caygeon were now below the water but it doesn't seem to have done much for the lake yet...  I finally have no snow in front of my garage so I can get out and about some with my handy-dandy electric scooter at 6 mph...LOL  Doc wanted me to start going for walks but after only going 3 driveways up the road , I had to head back home...legs and back started getting "ouchy"...

There's water in the creek today...  From the look at the docks there is about a foot deep of water near the front of them...not enough to dock a boat yet but it is coming ! Tried to take a picture but my camera got switched on to video by mistake and the batteries got drained ...only had enough juice to take this photo...
The north wind has pushed all the ice down the back channel... My old dock...still not enough water to dock a boat yet...
